Platinum now.
The PGM Markets
We see opportunity in the current market for low cost production with growing global demand.
Read More






Ready, set, produce.
Maseve Mine
On the Western Limb of the Bushveld Complex, the global hub of platinum production.
Read More






Engineering for growth
Waterberg Project
Strategic PGM discovery on the North Limb of the Bushveld Complex.
Read More

















Platinum Group Metals Ltd. is a mining company focused on the production of platinum and palladium. Our projects are located in the Bushveld Complex in South Africa, surrounded by 70% of the world’s platinum production.







Maseve Mine
The world’s newest platinum mine, Maseve, was commissioned in early 2016 and is a shallow, high grade operation.






Waterberg Project
A new discovery on the North Limb of the Bushveld complex, the Waterberg Project is being jointly developed by Platinum Group and the Japanese Government. 



Corporate Presentation
Please click below to view our latest presentation.












